							h3(class="panel-title") Why do we need gears? 
						div(class="panel-body") Gears do all sorts of things. A small motor can generate lots of power, but sometimes not enough to add torque (turning power).  When we reduce the output speed, we can increase torque.  Some other uses of gears are to reverse the direction of rotation, to synchronize the rotation of two axes, and to move motion to another axis.  
			div(class="row")
