						div(class="panel-heading")
							h3(class="panel-title") TASK: Identify the different types of gears
						div(class="panel-body") <strong>Spur Gears: </strong>The most common gear, they have straight teeth and are mounted on parallel Shafts. Spur gears can be combined to create very powerful gear reductions.
								img(src="/images/gears/spurgears.jpg")
								div( class="alert alert-info") <strong> Engineering tip:</strong> Gears are identified by their type and number of teeth. For example, the gears above, from left to right are: An 8 tooth spur gear, a 16 tooth spur gear, another 16 tooth spur gear, a 24 and 40 tooth spur gear. 
								p <strong>Helical Gears:</strong> Similar to spur gears, bevel gears have teeth  that are angled towards the gears face, giving them more contact in the same area. These gears are quieter than Spur gears.  
								img(src="/images/gears/Helical.jpg")			
								p <strong>Bevel Gears:</strong> Bevel gears are used to change the direction of the shaft. They are typicall designed to be mounted together at angles (90 degress is the most common). 
								img(src="/images/gears/tandstang.jpg")
								
			div(class="row")
